Add the following section to the repo AGENTS.md:

```
## Commit & Pull Request workflow
AGENT MUST ALWAYS FOLLOW this workflow.
- MUST ensure that changes are not on the main branch.
  - Ask to create a branch if not on a feature branch. Generate a branch name from context.
- MUST use atomic commits: tiny can be one final commit; medium/large should commit per meaningful step.
  - Follow Conventional Commit style (i.e. feat(scope): description)
  - Add a short description about the change and add a footer "Created by agent" in the body
- When the feature is deemed ready, create a pull request using `gh pr create`
  - Before PR: run project validation for medium/large work and any risky tiny change
  - Add a concise summary using conventional commits
  - Add a description of the changes using markdown. Highlight important topics with github callouts. Add prompts in a collapsible section with summary "Prompts used"; separate multiple prompts with a blank line. Summarize short answers and ignore irrelevant chatter.
  - For non-tiny work, send a Slack message to #trailblazers-codereview including the PR title and link
```

If there are any references to git workflows already - remove these in order to avoid confusion.
